div.p:
               I have the honor to submit herewith a memorandum from the treasury, according to which a sum of £30.3.8d is available yet for the Gov. Botanists Department at the Agent General's Office;

See R. Gudemann to M, 7 November 1887 (in this edition as 87-11-07b).
                and I would respectfully enquire, whether this amount could be utilized for the purchase of papier-mache models of fruits and other objects, illustrative of utilitarian plants and purchasable in Berlin.
